text: Helmed by a pair of elderly sisters who take great pride and care in their food as well as their stall. The food is delicately cut, tender and flavourful. The offal are well cleaned, suitably braised without the heavy taste of herbs. This is a kway chup we keep returning to, satiating us in comfort, palette and hearts.
A good and cheap kway chap. The service is a bit slow (been done by quite old aunties) but worth it.
